<h1> An Dramatically Innovative Chart or A Misleading One?  </h1>
By Luo Huiwen
<div>
<p>Issues related to gun shooting deaths are always hot potato for the U.S. society, therefore, related laws could usually hit the sensitive nerves of the "Stand Your Ground" law has once aroused big controversy.</p>
</div>
<p>Reuters have once published a <a href=” https://www.inside.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/07.jpg” >chart </a> as shown below (the original link seems to lose the graphic now)</p>
<div>
<p>At first glance without careful attention, one might easily be misled by the change of statistics of gun deaths in Florida in a reverse way since the Y-axis of the chart is reversed upside down – the lowest numerical value "0" is on the above and the highest numerical value "800" is at the bottom, which is quite to the opposite of one’s viewing and cognitive habits.</p>
</div>
